"{\"uid\": \"straitstimes.com-sport-stadiums-rise-at-paris-landmarks-100-days-from-olympics\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Choose edition  Search  singapore  asia  world  opinion  life  business  sport  Visual  Podcasts  SPH Rewards  STClassifieds  Paid press releases  Advertise with us  FAQs  Contact us  Sign up now:Get the biggest sports news in your inbox  Workers building up the bleachers in front of the obelisque at the construction site of La Concorde Urban Parc site for the upcoming Paris 2024 Olympics, in Paris on April 10, 2024.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 420, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 98, \"end\": 101, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Singapore_Press_Holdings\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.443516755798791e-14, \"text\": \"SPH\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Singapore_Press_Holdings\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Singapore_Press_Holdings\"}, {\"begin\": 147, \"end\": 156, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Advertise_(horse)\", \"score\": 0.9604822703099307, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Advertise\", \"types\": [\"Q7377\", \"Q729\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Advertise_(horse)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Advertise_(horse)\"}, {\"begin\": 330, \"end\": 338, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Place_de_la_Concorde\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.4511449566480663e-14, \"text\": \"Concorde\", \"types\": [\"Q34442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Place_de_la_Concorde\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Place_de_la_Concorde\"}, {\"begin\": 396, \"end\": 401, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.262692189040068e-24, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Urban Park will host street skateboarding, BMX freestyle, 3\\u00d73 basketball and Breaking Olympic events in the four arenas set up at central Paris' Place de La Concorde.\", \"from\": 421, \"to\": 591, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 468, \"end\": 481, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Freestyle_BMX\", \"score\": 0.9720209336867662, \"rank\": 0.028784427725423417, \"text\": \"BMX freestyle\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Freestyle_BMX\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Freestyle_BMX\"}, {\"begin\": 563, \"end\": 568, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.262692189040068e-24, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 570, \"end\": 590, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Place_de_la_Concorde\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.81173855639858e-27, \"text\": \"Place de La Concorde\", \"types\": [\"Q34442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Place_de_la_Concorde\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Place_de_la_Concorde\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"PHOTO: AFP  PublishedApr 15, 2024, 06:27 PM  UpdatedApr 15, 2024, 11:47 PM  PARIS-In front of the Eiffel Tower, stands are emerging from a tangle of scaffolding, while at the historic Place de la Concorde, forklift trucks buzz around carrying building materials.\", \"from\": 593, \"to\": 855, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 777, \"end\": 797, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Place_de_la_Concorde\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.81173855639858e-27, \"text\": \"Place de la Concorde\", \"types\": [\"Q34442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Place_de_la_Concorde\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Place_de_la_Concorde\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Across and around Paris, plans that have been on the drawing board for seven years since the city won the right to host the 2024 Olympics are turning into reality, 100 days from the start of the world's biggest sporting event.\", \"from\": 857, \"to\": 1083, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 875, \"end\": 880, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.262692189040068e-24, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The flurry of activity, including the hoisting of giant Olympic rings onto the Eiffel Tower, is giving Parisians the chance to glimpse for the first time how the 17-day extravaganza will transform the city.\", \"from\": 1085, \"to\": 1291, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"You can see them putting the infrastructure up,\\\" said sports fan and Paris resident Valentin Fargier, 27.\", \"from\": 1293, \"to\": 1399, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1363, \"end\": 1368, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.262692189040068e-24, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The city's being tidied up and the monuments are clean.\", \"from\": 1400, \"to\": 1456, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It's going to be great.\\\"\", \"from\": 1457, \"to\": 1481, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Unlike in previous Olympics, only two new permanent sports venues have been built for Paris 2024 in a deliberate change of strategy to make the Games cheaper and more \\\"sober\\\".\", \"from\": 1483, \"to\": 1658, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1569, \"end\": 1579, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.853368881899899e-30, \"text\": \"Paris 2024\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"An 8,000-seat arena that will host badminton and rhythmic gymnastics was inaugurated in a deprived part of northern Paris in February, while President Emmanuel Macron cut the ribbon at a new aquatics centre in a nearby suburb on April 4.\", \"from\": 1660, \"to\": 1897, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1776, \"end\": 1781, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.262692189040068e-24, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 1811, \"end\": 1826, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Emmanuel Macron\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Elsewhere, 95 per cent of the sports are set to take place in existing venues, or in the temporary stands that are sprouting like mushrooms ahead of the start of the Games on July 26 and the Paralympics on Aug 28.\", \"from\": 1899, \"to\": 2112, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Beach volleyball will be played in front of the Eiffel Tower, with archery at the Invalides monument.\", \"from\": 2114, \"to\": 2215, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2196, \"end\": 2205, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Les_Invalides\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.693067738666258e-48, \"text\": \"Invalides\", \"types\": [\"Q41176\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Les_Invalides\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Les_Invalides\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Skateboarding will take place at Place de la Concorde and the Chateau de Versailles will host the equestrian events.\", \"from\": 2216, \"to\": 2332, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2249, \"end\": 2269, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Place_de_la_Concorde\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.81173855639858e-27, \"text\": \"Place de la Concorde\", \"types\": [\"Q34442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Place_de_la_Concorde\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Place_de_la_Concorde\"}, {\"begin\": 2278, \"end\": 2299, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Palace_of_Versailles\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Chateau de Versailles\", \"types\": [\"Q41176\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Palace_of_Versailles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Palace_of_Versailles\"}, {\"begin\": 2314, \"end\": 2324, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Equestrianism\", \"score\": 0.9998428835460462, \"rank\": 0.000157141136314739, \"text\": \"equestrian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Equestrianism\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Equestrianism\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In total, 200,000 seats are being installed in temporary venues.\", \"from\": 2334, \"to\": 2398, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The River Seine will host the open-water swimming - pollution permitting - as well as the spectacular opening ceremony that will see teams sail down it in a flotilla of boats in front of up to half a million spectators.\", \"from\": 2400, \"to\": 2619, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2404, \"end\": 2415, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"River Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Mr Macron, however, said for the first time on April 15 that there are alternative plans in the event of a security threat.\", \"from\": 2620, \"to\": 2743, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2623, \"end\": 2629, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.290504519340851e-15, \"text\": \"Macron\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Organisers insist that everything from the infrastructure to their budget is under control.\", \"from\": 2745, \"to\": 2836, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We are ready for this final straight,\\\" chief organiser Tony Estanguet said at a press conference to mark the 100-day countdown.\", \"from\": 2838, \"to\": 2966, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2894, \"end\": 2908, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tony_Estanguet\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Tony Estanguet\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tony_Estanguet\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tony_Estanguet\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We have built up a lot of confidence and peace of mind.\\\"\", \"from\": 2967, \"to\": 3024, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"He noted that construction work was often \\\"the biggest challenge that poses problems for the organisation of the Games\\\".\", \"from\": 3026, \"to\": 3146, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The timetable has been perfectly respected, which is a relief for us,\\\" he said.\", \"from\": 3148, \"to\": 3228, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"While the world-renowned architecture of the French capital will serve as a stunning backdrop to the Games, the city's often hard-to-please residents appear in no mood for a party yet.\", \"from\": 3230, \"to\": 3414, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3275, \"end\": 3281, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.785983467068065, \"rank\": 0.18993218861712965, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Media coverage has been dominated in recent months by ongoing grumbling about high ticket prices, the cost to taxpayers, strike threats, as well as the planned increase in fares on the creaking Paris metro system during the Games.\", \"from\": 3416, \"to\": 3646, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3610, \"end\": 3615, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.262692189040068e-24, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Many wealthier Parisians plan to be on holiday for the duration of the event, often to cash in on the riches being offered on apartment-renting websites such as Airbnb.\", \"from\": 3648, \"to\": 3816, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3809, \"end\": 3815, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Airbnb\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Airbnb\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Airbnb\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Airbnb\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Will it be a case of the city and nation finding collective pride once a global TV audience of billions begin admiring the landmarks, the shimmering water of the Seine, or the rebuilt spire of the fire-damaged Notre-Dame cathedral?\", \"from\": 3818, \"to\": 4049, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3980, \"end\": 3985, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.0128944359480547e-17, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"If everything goes well at this difficult moment, if the organisation is good, if French athletes win medals, it might create a moment of national pride,\\\" said French sports historian Paul Dietschy from the University of Bourgogne-Franche-Comte.\", \"from\": 4051, \"to\": 4297, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4134, \"end\": 4140, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.785983467068065, \"rank\": 0.18993218861712965, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 4212, \"end\": 4218, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.785983467068065, \"rank\": 0.18993218861712965, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But he warned it would be \\\"ephemeral, like the sport itself\\\".\", \"from\": 4299, \"to\": 4360, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Meanwhile, the Olympic flame will be lit in ancient Olympia on April 16 for a torch relay stretching from the Acropolis to French Polynesia.\", \"from\": 4362, \"to\": 4502, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4414, \"end\": 4421, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympia_London\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 9.04622037634652e-16, \"text\": \"Olympia\", \"types\": [\"Q41176\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympia_London\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympia_London\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Spectators will be able to attend the torch-relay events, after being banned during the Covid-19 pandemic-affected Tokyo Olympics in 2021.AFP    Olympics 2024  Paralympics  France  Olympics  E-paper  Newsletters  Podcasts  RSS Feed  About Us  Terms & Conditions  Personal Data Protection Notice  Need help?\", \"from\": 4504, \"to\": 4810, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4619, \"end\": 4633, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999999999995453, \"rank\": 5.03661040541245e-13, \"text\": \"Tokyo Olympics\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2020_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 4677, \"end\": 4683, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999994177111934, \"rank\": 4.771527613744537e-07, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 4727, 